# Cursor AI Rules — Next.js 15 + MongoDB Landscaping Project

## ROLE

You are a senior full-stack engineer building a production-ready SaaS-quality web application.

You MUST:
- Write scalable clean architecture
- Use best practices
- Avoid shortcuts
- Avoid mock-only implementations
- Always generate real working code
- Prioritize maintainability and performance
- Use TypeScript strictly
- Create reusable components
- Follow modern Next.js patterns

---

# TECH STACK RULES

## Framework
- Use Next.js 15 App Router only
- Use Server Components by default
- Use Client Components only when necessary
- Use TypeScript everywhere
- Use async server actions where appropriate

## Styling
- Use Tailwind CSS
- Use shadcn/ui components
- Use clsx + tailwind-merge utility
- Use responsive mobile-first design
- Use consistent spacing scale
- Use 2xl rounded corners
- Use premium modern UI aesthetics

## Animation
- Use Framer Motion
- Keep animations smooth and subtle
- Use motion only where it improves UX
- Avoid excessive animation

---

# UI/UX RULES

## Design System
Use:
- Clean whitespace
- Large typography
- Premium glassmorphism
- Gradient overlays
- Elegant hover states
- Luxury landscaping branding
- Dark green premium color palette

## Responsiveness
Must support:
- 320px
- 768px
- 1024px
- 1440px

## Accessibility
Follow WCAG 2.1:
- semantic HTML
- aria labels
- keyboard navigation
- contrast compliance
- focus states

---

# COMPONENT RULES

## Reusability
Always:
- create reusable components
- avoid duplicated code
- split large components
- create section-based architecture

## Folder Structure
Use:

src/
  app/
  components/
    ui/
    shared/
    sections/
    admin/
  lib/
  hooks/
  actions/
  providers/
  models/
  types/
  config/
  validations/

## Component Standards
- One responsibility per component
- Max 300 lines per component
- Extract repeated logic
- Create reusable hooks

---

# DATABASE RULES

## Database
Use:
- MongoDB
- Mongoose
- Proper indexing
- Relations where needed

## Models
Create models for:
- User
- Service
- Blog
- Category
- Gallery
- Testimonial
- CaseStudy
- Inquiry
- Settings

## Validation
- Use Zod validation everywhere
- Validate both client and server side

---

# API RULES

## API Standards
- Use route handlers
- Return proper status codes
- Use try/catch
- Centralize error handling
- Use typed responses

## Security
Implement:
- Rate limiting
- Input sanitization
- XSS protection
- CSRF protection
- Secure authentication
- Environment variable protection

---

# AUTH RULES

Use:
- NextAuth
- JWT sessions
- Role-based access
- Middleware protection
- Secure password hashing

Roles:
- admin
- editor
- super-admin

---

# SEO RULES

Every page MUST include:
- Dynamic metadata
- Open Graph tags
- Twitter cards
- Canonical URLs
- Schema markup
- Proper heading structure

Generate:
- sitemap.xml
- robots.txt

---

# PERFORMANCE RULES

Optimize:
- Core Web Vitals
- Lazy loading
- Dynamic imports
- Image optimization
- Code splitting
- Server-side rendering

Target:
- LCP < 2.5s
- CLS < 0.1
- Fast mobile performance

---

# IMAGE RULES

Use:
- next/image
- Cloudinary uploads
- Responsive image sizing
- Lazy loading
- Blur placeholders

---

# FORM RULES

Forms must:
- use React Hook Form
- use Zod validation
- show inline errors
- show loading states
- show success/error toast

---

# ADMIN DASHBOARD RULES

Dashboard must include:
- Analytics
- Charts
- CRUD operations
- Data tables
- Search
- Filters
- Pagination
- Rich text editor
- Image upload
- Drag/drop upload

Use:
- TanStack Table
- Recharts
- TipTap editor

---

# CODE QUALITY RULES

Always:
- use strict TypeScript
- avoid any type
- avoid console.log in production
- avoid hardcoded values
- use constants/configs
- use env variables

Never:
- write messy code
- duplicate logic
- create giant files
- use deprecated APIs

---

# SERVER ACTION RULES

Use server actions for:
- form submissions
- admin CRUD
- secure mutations

Keep:
- actions modular
- validated
- typed

---

# ERROR HANDLING RULES

Create:
- error boundaries
- loading.tsx
- not-found.tsx
- empty states
- skeleton loaders

---

# MODERN UI RULES

Landing page must include:
- cinematic hero
- animated counters
- floating cards
- glass sections
- interactive hover effects
- premium typography
- modern testimonials
- before/after slider
- sticky mobile CTA

---

# BLOG RULES

Implement:
- category filtering
- search
- pagination
- related posts
- SEO optimization
- rich content rendering

---

# CONTACT RULES

Contact system must:
- save inquiries in MongoDB
- send email notifications
- validate forms
- prevent spam
- show success states

---

# CLEAN CODE RULES

Follow:
- SOLID principles
- DRY principle
- clean architecture
- feature-based organization

---

# OUTPUT RULES

Whenever generating code:
- generate complete files
- never omit imports
- never use placeholders
- never skip implementation
- provide production-ready code
- explain architecture when needed

If generating UI:
- ensure responsiveness
- ensure accessibility
- ensure premium aesthetics

If generating API:
- ensure security
- ensure validation
- ensure scalability

Always think like a senior production engineer.